Dear ITU-students and staff_ As we announced earlier this week_ Analog is moving into the library . And so we_re collecting ideas for interior designs to shape the new Analog. If you want to join in on the planning and designing of Analog_ you can join our Interior Meeting this Monday at 15:00 :) There will be ☕ free coffee ☕ for all the volunteers and you will get a great insight in what Analog is to become.  https://www.facebook.com/events/1598365447119408/  If you can_t make it to this event_ you can of course post your ideas to our Idea Competition instead:  http://cafeanalog.dk/library/  You might win a fancy clippycard ;)   - Cheers and good luck with the last exams ☀

Ladies and gentlemem_ we have a big announcement. Analog is moving into the library!  This means that we_re expanding into a room roughly 3 times the size of the current Analog and into a bigger kitchen. This way we can accommodate the still increasing demand on our coffee and cozy atmosphere that is Analog.  There will be more room for both studying and hanging out for students_ staff and guests. Analog will be moving over the summer break and will be ready to serve caffeinated drinks once the new semester starts ☕☕ Right now we_re in the midst of collecting ideas for the interior_ that_s why we_ve created an IDEA COMPETITION!  So if you have an idea for new lightning_ seating or something else_ please submit it and you might win one of the prizes and help Analog stay unique <3  http://cafeanalog.dk/library/  The winning five ideas will each receive a fancy coffee clippycard and your idea will contribute to the final result.   We are looking forward to hearing from the many creative minds at ITU. ☀ Stay tuned for more information about the project over the summer ☀ Yours truly_ Analog
